AUDIO: 'this is called Anchorwave, and this can generate&nbsp; interactive world videos. In other words, this is&nbsp;&nbsp; a video where you can press the WD or arrow keys&nbsp; and move around this 3D world. So, it just takes a&nbsp;&nbsp; starting initial frame and then you can generate a&nbsp; 3D world from that where you can move around. Now,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'currently for one iteration, it can only generate&nbsp; 81 frames, which is roughly a few seconds,&nbsp;&nbsp; but you can iterate this multiple times to create&nbsp; a longer video. The really impressive thing is it&nbsp;&nbsp; can maintain consistency and realism over a long&nbsp; period of time. Here are some other examples for&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your reference. Notice that this is much better&nbsp; than previous interactive world generators in that&nbsp;&nbsp; this one actually preserves a memory of the scene.&nbsp; So even if you look away and then you look back,&nbsp;&nbsp; everything remains the same as before. And then&nbsp; here are a few other examples. And as you can see,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it doesn\'t just have to work in a first-person&nbsp; view. You can also upload a thirderson perspective&nbsp;&nbsp; like this. And it can also generate a third person&nbsp; video of this character moving around. The key to&nbsp;&nbsp; anchor weave is that it uses a special technique&nbsp; called local geometric memories to generate the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
